The paper deals with recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of contextual information also relates to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves data management and representation, which are topics covered in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the use of association rules suggests a possible connection to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category, although this is less likely than the other categories mentioned.
